
Ingredients:

Pizza dough
1 cup tomato sauce
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
Assorted vegetables (such as bell peppers, onions, mushrooms, olives, etc.)
Olive oil
Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions:
Preheat your oven to 450°F (230°C).
Roll out the pizza dough and place it on a pizza stone or baking sheet.
Spread the tomato sauce evenly over the dough.
Sprinkle the shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce.
Arrange the assorted vegetables on top of the cheese.
Drizzle olive oil over the vegetables and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is melted and bubbly.
Remove from the oven and let it cool slightly before slicing and serving.
